text: Private High-Desert Oasis - Off-Grid Living with Endless PossibilitiesTucked away in its own secluded valley and surrounded by dramatic granite boulders, this 40-acre hideout offers unmatched privacy, natural beauty, and the freedom of off-grid living. Once a thriving organic farm, the land is rich with potential, having previously produced a variety of grapes and vegetables. At an elevation of 4,400 feet, the climate is ideal--mild and comfortable across all four seasons--making it perfect for sustainable living or a peaceful retreat from the hustle of city life.The main residence is a thoughtfully designed 1,150-square-foot, two-bedroom, one-bath home built with 12-inch AAC block walls, providing excellent insulation to keep it cool in the summer and warm in the winter. Inside, the open living space features stained concrete floors, a cozy wood-burning stove, and gas appliances. A spacious 800-square-foot covered porch invites you to relax and take in the stunning natural surroundings. Just a short walk from the home, you'll find a wood-fired hot tub--an ideal place to unwind under the stars.A short distance from the main house sits an 860-square-foot barn with a 400-square-foot covered porch, two horse stalls, storage areas, and a guest suite with a half-bath--perfect for visitors or additional living space.Also on the property is an impressive, unfinished 3,700-square-foot workshop built from concrete block. This versatile structure features four large rooms. With one room (720 sqft) plumbed for a kitchen and full bath and another room (530 sqft) plumbed for a half bath and additional drain for sink or washer/dryer, you could have a 1250sqft apartment. Workshop also includes a 500-square-foot underground, two-room cellar--offering endless potential for creative or practical use, from winemaking to cold storage or future expansion.This is a great opportunity to create a generational property and invest in your future for years to come!Water is one of the property's standout features. A seasonal stream runs through the land, and you'll also find two ponds, three wells, and a gravity-flow water system. A classic 14-foot Aeromotor windmill adds a timeless touch and functionality to the off-grid lifestyle.Accessed via a private, end-of-the-road entrance with a locked ranch gate, this property offers total seclusion while still being just a 30-minute drive from all the amenities of Prescott. Whether you're seeking a private sanctuary, a sustainable homestead, or a unique investment opportunity, this one-of-a-kind property is ready for its next caretaker.This is more than just a home--it's a lifestyle. Come experience the peace, privacy, and potential of this remarkable desert retreat. This one-of-a-kind property is a must-see. Start your next chapter here.
formatted_address: 1320 S Grisby Rd, Skull Valley, AZ, 86338

text: Your search for a haven of tranquility ends here. This 3 bedroom, 2 bath home is the perfect place to beat the heat and enjoy 4 mild seasons. Custom designed and built to maximize comfort, structural integrity, and longevity. From the 12-inch thick, fireproof RASTRA construction to the metal roofing and meticulous landscaping, you will find peace and ease of maintenance for many years to come. With a walk-in pantry in the kitchen, large dedicated laundry room, and spacious master closet, you will never lack for space and organizational capacity. The in-floor heat operates via the on-demand gas water heater, making those winter months comfortable. The custom staircase off the front entry brings you to a classy loft area with gorgeous bookshelves - perfect for an office, library, or other flex space. For the chef of the home, you will love the Sub-Zero refrigerator and Wolf professional gas stovetop with electric oven. The large island makes food prep a dream with a built-in prep sink, and the open concept to the living room keeps you involved in the activities of the home. The large 2-car garage is perfect for parking, projects, and storage! Outside are 2 lush grassy lawns, established shade trees, and lovely but functional landscaping. Behind the house, step out of your fenced yard and across a small seasonal wash to a beautiful meadow surrounded by cottonwoods. This could be the perfect place for your larger 4-legged friends, or left as is! All this and more in a tidy 2-acre package just a short distance from Prescott.
formatted_address: 770 S Grisby Rd, Skull Valley, AZ, 86338

text: Set on over three acres of level, usable land in peaceful Skull Valley, Arizona, this unique country property offers endless potential and classic rural charm. The parcel features a 625 sq ft, 1-bedroom, 1-bathroom home along with multiple outbuildings, including sheds, a greenhouse, barn, well house, and a one-car carport--ideal for storage, projects, or agricultural use. Whether you're looking to renovate the existing home, expand it, or build a brand-new residence, this property provides the space and flexibility to bring your vision to life.Enjoy sweeping views of Black Mountain and the natural beauty of a seasonal wash running along the boundary line. With open fields and a strong well, the land is perfectly suited for horses, goats, chickens, or even that cow you've always wanted. The west-facing back porch is the perfect spot to relax and take in Arizona's stunning sunsets and temperate climate.The property is well established with mature fruit trees, including apple, cherry, peach, apricot, plum, and walnut. A rose garden and fragrant lavender add vibrant color throughout the spring and summer, while the rich soil makes this an excellent location for gardening. This is a rare opportunity to own a versatile, scenic country property with room to grow, create, and enjoy the quiet beauty of Arizona living.

text: Historic & picturesque Four Cross Ranch, located 20 miles SW of Prescott & 2 hours from Phoenix. Ranch spans a total of 1, 576 deeded acres, w/additional 4, 033 acres of BLM & State Land grazing leases, making it ideal for ranching, recreation & hunting. Perched on a hill, the main residence offers panoramic views of rolling pastures & distant mountains, creating a serene vantage point, along with 4 more homes for guests and ranch hands. Ranch is efficiently watered by multiple wells & offers top-notch facilities for cattle & horses, including a 14-stall enclosed barn, a two-stall shedrow barn w/spacious outdoor runs & an open-air barn with W panels. Complete w/tack room, office, round pen & cutting and roping arenas. Multiple workshops and equipment sheds provide ample space for all ranching activities. The large shop features three-phase electric power. Historically significant, the ranch was once partially owned by Virgil and Elvira Earp during the Territory of Arizona era. Scattered throughout the land, you may stumble upon ancient petroglyphs. Whether you're drawn to its rich history, exceptional livestock facilities, or the serene beauty of its surroundings, Four Cross Ranch is a legacy of excellence waiting to be explored. Main Residence 4289 sq/ft (3bed/3.5bath) Modular Home 1900 sq/ft (3bed/2bath) Modular Home 1900 sq/ft (3bed/2bath) Guest House 1806 sq/ft (2bed/2bed) Guest House 3574 sq/ft (3bed/2bed)
formatted_address: 5500 S Four Cross Ranch Rd, Skull Valley, AZ, 86338
